The prezygapophyses differ from previous cervicals in that they form a more accute angle with the vertebral body and have a flat, dorsally directed articular surface in lateral view (
Fig. 8A, B
). The beams supporting the prezygapophyseal articular surface are stout, as in the previous cervicals. The prezygapophyses are inverted V-shaped in anterior view (
Fig. 8F
