In anterior view, the dorsal rim of the anterior articular surface is well developed, and shows a slight indentation below the neural canal, giving it a small heartshape as in the more anterior caudals ( Fig. 27D ). In posterior view, the articular surface of the centrum is round, and shows pronounced round striations on the rim ( Fig. 27E ). In lateral view, the centrum displays a larger anterior articular surface than posteriorly ( Fig. 27A, B ), as in other middle caudals of eusauropods (
Upchurch et al. 2004
