The neural spine is straight, and increases in axial width towards the summit (
Fig. 27A, B, F
). It is more inclined posteriorly than dorsally, confirming its middle-posterior caudal position. On the lateral side, rugose dorsoventrally positioned striations are visible. The spine summit is not straight, but shows a faint saddle shape (
